1. DEFINITIONS

"Software" means the Emet investigative journalism framework, including
all source code, documentation, configuration files, test suites, and
associated materials in this repository.

"Licensor" means Liberation Labs / The THCoalition, the copyright holder.

"You" means the individual or entity exercising rights under this License.

"Qualifying Journalism Use" means use of the Software exclusively for the
purpose of investigative journalism, press freedom advocacy, or
anti-corruption research by a Qualifying Organization.

"Qualifying Organization" means any of the following, provided that the
organization adheres to recognized journalistic ethics standards
(including but not limited to the SPJ Code of Ethics, the OCCRP
Editorial Standards, the IFJ Global Charter of Ethics for Journalists,
or equivalent professional codes):

  (a) A newsroom, media outlet, or journalistic enterprise whose primary
      purpose is the production and publication of journalism in the
      public interest, operating with editorial independence from
      political parties, government entities, and advocacy campaigns;
  (b) A member, partner, or affiliate of the Global Investigative
      Journalism Network (GIJN), the Organized Crime and Corruption
      Reporting Project (OCCRP), the International Consortium of
      Investigative Journalists (ICIJ), or successor organizations;
  (c) A press freedom organization, including but not limited to the
      Committee to Protect Journalists (CPJ), Reporters Without Borders
      (RSF/Reporters Sans Frontières), the Freedom of the Press
      Foundation, or equivalent national or regional bodies;
  (d) An academic institution operating a journalism program, media
      research center, or press freedom clinic;
  (e) A nonprofit organization whose stated mission includes
      anti-corruption, government transparency, corporate accountability,
      or protection of whistleblowers;
  (f) An individual freelance journalist who can demonstrate a bona fide
      journalistic purpose and a track record of published investigative
      work.

An organization does NOT qualify if its primary activities include:
  (i)   Conducting deceptive operations, entrapment, or infiltration
        targeting private individuals, advocacy organizations, or
        political opponents rather than investigating matters of
        genuine public interest;
  (ii)  Producing content primarily intended to serve the electoral,
        legislative, or political strategy of a political party,
        political campaign, political action committee, or government
        entity;
  (iii) Systematic harassment, doxxing, or intimidation of private
        individuals, including through selective or deceptive editing
        of recorded material;
  (iv)  Operating under the direction or financial control of a
        political party, government agency, or intelligence service;
  (v)   Presenting news-themed entertainment, commentary, or opinion
        programming as journalism, particularly where the organization
        or its representatives have asserted in legal proceedings,
        regulatory filings, or public statements that its content
        does not constitute factual reporting, should not be taken as
        statements of fact, or is intended as entertainment or opinion
        rather than news.

The Licensor reserves the right, exercisable in good faith, to make
final determinations regarding Qualifying Organization status.

"Commercial Use" means any use of the Software that does not qualify as
Qualifying Journalism Use, including but not limited to: compliance
screening, know-your-customer (KYC) processes, anti-money-laundering
(AML) operations, due diligence services, corporate intelligence,
litigation support, risk advisory, or integration into any product or
service offered for profit.


2. SOURCE AVAILABILITY

The source code of the Software is made publicly available for the
purposes of inspection, security auditing, academic study, and
transparency. Public availability of the source code does not constitute
a grant of rights beyond those explicitly stated in this License.


