5. ETHICAL USE RESTRICTIONS

Regardless of whether You hold a journalism license or a commercial
license, You may NOT use the Software, in whole or in part, directly
or indirectly, for any of the following purposes:

  (a) SURVEILLANCE OF JOURNALISTS AND SOURCES — To surveil, monitor,
      track, identify, or profile journalists, media workers, editorial
      staff, or their confidential sources, informants, or
      whistleblowers.

  (b) PRESS SUPPRESSION — To suppress, censor, restrict, delay, or
      interfere with the publication of journalism or investigative
      findings, or to facilitate prior restraint of publication.

  (c) RETALIATION — To identify, target, harass, intimidate, or
      retaliate against whistleblowers, sources of investigative
      reporting, or individuals who have provided information to
      journalists or anti-corruption bodies.

  (d) CIRCUMVENTION OF PRESS PROTECTIONS — To circumvent, undermine, or
      defeat legal protections for journalistic privilege, source
      confidentiality, shield laws, or freedom of information rights.

  (e) MASS SURVEILLANCE — To conduct mass surveillance, population-scale
      monitoring, or bulk data collection on civilian populations,
      whether by state or non-state actors.

  (f) TARGETING VULNERABLE POPULATIONS — To target, profile, or
      discriminate against individuals or groups on the basis of race,
      ethnicity, religion, gender, sexual orientation, disability,
      immigration status, or political opinion.

  (g) WEAPONS AND VIOLENCE — To develop, support, or facilitate weapons
      systems, military targeting, or acts of violence against any
      person.

These restrictions are grounded in:
  - The Universal Declaration of Human Rights, Articles 12, 18, and 19
  - The European Convention on Human Rights, Article 10
  - The Inter-American Declaration of Principles on Freedom of Expression
  - The African Charter on Human and Peoples' Rights, Article 9
  - The UN Plan of Action on the Safety of Journalists

Violation of any Ethical Use Restriction constitutes an automatic and
immediate termination of all rights granted under this License and any
commercial license agreement, without notice.


